{"TopicId":146373,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Accessing specific drag cube information in the VAB/SPH","CreatedByName":"Nertea","CreatedById":83952,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T20:31:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nertea","CreatedById":83952,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T20:31:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to access some part drag cube parameters in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E to show things to the player. Specifically I\u0027m looking\u00A0for:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Epart.DragCubes.WeightedSize \npart.DragCubes.WeightedArea\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, these two fields are only populated in flight. Can these be force-calculated in the editor, or does anyone understand how I might go about calculating them manually?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMight need to page \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0here, I expect he knows the most...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T22:46:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCalling\u00A0part.DragCubes.SetDragWeights() should do it but I have no idea how it will react in the editor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Boris-Barboris","CreatedById":133181,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T23:15:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Boris-Barboris/CorrectCoL/blob/master/CoLMarkerFull.cs#L80\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Boris-Barboris/CorrectCoL/blob/master/CoLMarkerFull.cs#L80\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nMight help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nertea","CreatedById":83952,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-23T16:40:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorks like a charm, thanks guys!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}